{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849592379,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e23469001Zl0JJvB4jRC3qY","messageID":"msg_d78e226b70010vezKKvbv5256s","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_e3f1ca52758c49db8673dc95","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Functional Requirements\n10: \n11: 1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n12: 2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n13: 3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n14: 4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n15: 5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n16: 6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n17: \n18: ### Non-Functional Requirements\n19: \n20: 1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99\n21: 2. **Scalability**: Support 10,000+ concurrent sessions\n22: 3. **Reliability**: Session data persisted in Redis for recovery\n23: 4. **Thread Safety**: Safe concurrent access from multiple goroutines\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ### Component Structure\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/router/\n31: ├── router.go                      # Main router implementation\n32: ├── router_test.go                 # Unit tests\n33: ├── handler.go                     # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n34: ├── handler_test.go                # Handler tests\n35: ├── resolver.go                    # Route resolution logic\n36: ├── resolver_test.go               # Resolver tests\n37: ├── health.go                      # Health check manager\n38: ├── health_test.go                 # Health check tests\n39: ├── config.go                      # Configuration structures\n40: ├── types.go                       # Type definitions\n41: ├── session/                       # NEW: Session management package\n42: │   ├── manager.go                 # Session manager implementation\n43: │   ├── manager_test.go            # Manager tests\n44: │   ├── session.go                 # Session data structure\n45: │   ├── session_test.go            # Session tests\n46: │   ├── store.go                   # Session storage interface\n47: │   ├── store_test.go              # Store tests\n48: │   ├── redis_store.go             # Redis-backed session store\n49: │   ├── redis_store_test.go        # Redis store tests\n50: │   ├── memory_store.go            # In-memory session store (dev/test)\n51: │   ├── memory_store_test.go       # Memory store tests\n52: │   └── config.go                  # Session configuration\n53: └── middleware/                    # NEW: HTTP middleware\n54:     ├── session_middleware.go      # Session extraction/attachment\n55:     ├── session_middleware_test.go # Middleware tests\n56:     └── auth_middleware.go         # Authentication middleware\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Integration Points\n60: \n61: - **Session Store**: Redis (production) or in-memory (dev/test) for session persistence\n62: - **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n63: - **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources\n64: - **Existing Router**: Extends AR-009 router with session-aware routing\n65: \n66: ### High-Level Flow\n67: \n68: ```\n69: ┌─────────────┐\n70: │   Client    │\n71: └──────┬──────┘\n72:        │ HTTP Request (with/without session token)\n73:        ▼\n74: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n75: │   Session Middleware            │\n76: │   - Extract session token       │\n77: │   - Validate session            │\n78: │   - Attach to context           │\n79: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n80:                │\n81:                ▼\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │   Handler                       │\n84: │   - Check session affinity      │\n85: │   - Resolve backend             │\n86: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n87:                │\n88:                ▼\n89: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n90: │   Session Manager               │\n91: │   - Get/Create session          │\n92: │   - Update last activity        │\n93: │   - Bind to backend             │\n94: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n95:                │\n96:                ▼\n97: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n98: │   Resolver                      │\n99: │   - Look up route entry         │\n100: │   - Apply session affinity      │\n101: └──────────────┬──────────────────┘\n102:                │\n103:                ▼\n104: ┌─────────────────────────────────┐\n105: │   Backend (AgentRuntime/CI)     │\n106: │   - Proxy request               │\n107: └─────────────────────────────────┘\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Session Lifecycle\n111: \n112: ```\n113: ┌──────────────┐\n114: │   Created    │ (first request or explicit creation)\n115: └──────┬───────┘\n116:        │\n117:        ▼\n118: ┌──────────────┐\n119: │   Active     │ (requests being processed)\n120: └──────┬───────┘\n121:        │\n122:        ├─ Idle Timeout ──▶ ┌──────────────┐\n123:        │                   │   Expired    │\n124:        ├─ Max Duration ──▶ └──────┬───────┘\n125:        │                          │\n126:        ▼                          ▼\n127: ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐\n128: │  Terminated  │◀─────────│  Cleanup     │\n129: └──────────────┘  (delete) └──────────────┘\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Data Structures\n133: \n134: ### Session\n135: \n136: ```go\n137: type Session struct {\n138:     // Unique session identifier\n139:     ID string `json:\"id\"`\n140:     \n141:     // Namespace of the backend resource\n142:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n143:     \n144:     // Backend kind: \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n145:     Kind string `json:\"kind\"`\n146:     \n147:     // Name of the backend resource\n148:     BackendName string `json:\"backendName\"`\n149:     \n150:     // Backend URL for routing\n151:     BackendURL string `json:\"backendURL\"`\n152:     \n153:     // User identifier (from auth token or request header)\n154:     UserID string `json:\"userId\"`\n155:     \n156:     // Session creation time\n157:     CreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n158:     \n159:     // Last activity timestamp\n160:     LastActivityAt time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n161:     \n162:     // Session expiration time (CreatedAt + MaxDuration)\n163:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n164:     \n165:     // Session state\n166:     State SessionState `json:\"state\"`\n167:     \n168:     // Metadata for extensibility\n169:     Metadata map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n170:     \n171:     // Lock for concurrent access\n172:     mu sync.RWMutex\n173: }\n174: \n175: type SessionState string\n176: \n177: const (\n178:     SessionStateActive     SessionState = \"Active\"\n179:     SessionStateIdle       SessionState = \"Idle\"\n180:     SessionStateExpired    SessionState = \"Expired\"\n181:     SessionStateTerminated SessionState = \"Terminated\"\n182: )\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ### SessionConfig\n186: \n187: ```go\n188: type SessionConfig struct {\n189:     // Enable session management\n190:     Enabled bool\n191:     \n192:     // Session cookie name\n193:     CookieName string\n194:     \n195:     // Session cookie domain (optional)\n196:     CookieDomain string\n197:     \n198:     // Session cookie path\n199:     CookiePath string\n200:     \n201:     // Session cookie secure flag\n202:     CookieSecure bool\n203:     \n204:     // Session cookie HTTP-only flag\n205:     CookieHTTPOnly bool\n206:     \n207:     // Session cookie SameSite policy\n208:     CookieSameSite http.SameSite\n209:     \n210:     // Session token header name\n211:     TokenHeader string\n212:     \n213:     // Maximum session duration\n214:     MaxDuration time.Duration\n215:     \n216:     // Idle session timeout\n217:     IdleTimeout time.Duration\n218:     \n219:     // Session cleanup interval\n220:     CleanupInterval time.Duration\n221:     \n222:     // Store type: \"redis\" or \"memory\"\n223:     StoreType string\n224:     \n225:     // Redis configuration\n226:     Redis RedisSessionConfig\n227: }\n228: \n229: type RedisSessionConfig struct {\n230:     // Redis address\n231:     Addr string\n232:     \n233:     // Redis password\n234:     Password string\n235:     \n236:     // Redis database number\n237:     DB int\n238:     \n239:     // Session key prefix\n240:     KeyPrefix string\n241:     \n242:     // Connection pool size\n243:     PoolSize int\n244:     \n245:     // Connection timeout\n246:     DialTimeout time.Duration\n247:     \n248:     // Read timeout\n249:     ReadTimeout time.Duration\n250:     \n251:     // Write timeout\n252:     WriteTimeout time.Duration\n253: }\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### SessionManager\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: type SessionManager struct {\n260:     config    *SessionConfig\n261:     store     SessionStore\n262:     metrics   *SessionMetrics\n263:     stopCh    chan struct{}\n264:     wg        sync.WaitGroup\n265:     mu        sync.RWMutex\n266: }\n267: \n268: type SessionStore interface {\n269:     // Get retrieves a session by ID\n270:     Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n271:     \n272:     // Set stores or updates a session\n273:     Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n274:     \n275:     // Delete removes a session\n276:     Delete(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n277:     \n278:     // List returns sessions matching namespace and kind\n279:     List(ctx context.Context, namespace, kind string) ([]*Session, error)\n280:     \n281:     // ListByUser returns sessions for a specific user\n282:     ListByUser(ctx context.Context, userID string) ([]*Session, error)\n283:     \n284:     // Close closes the store connection\n285:     Close() error\n286: }\n287: \n288: type SessionMetrics struct {\n289:     ActiveSessions   prometheus.Gauge\n290:     SessionsCreated  prometheus.Counter\n291:     SessionsExpired  prometheus.Counter\n292:     SessionsTerminated prometheus.Counter\n293:     SessionDuration  prometheus.Histogram\n294:     StoreLatency     prometheus.Histogram\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### SessionMiddleware\n299: \n300: ```go\n301: type SessionMiddleware struct {\n302:     manager *SessionManager\n303:     config  *SessionConfig\n304: }\n305: \n306: // ExtractSession extracts session from request\n307: func (m *SessionMiddleware) ExtractSession(r *http.Request) (string, error)\n308: \n309: // AttachSession attaches session to response\n310: func (m *SessionMiddleware) AttachSession(w http.ResponseWriter, session *Session)\n311: \n312: // WithSession wraps handler with session context\n313: func (m *SessionMiddleware) WithSession(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ## API Contracts\n317: \n318: ### Session Token Format\n319: \n320: **Cookie-based (default):**\n321: ```\n322: Set-Cookie: agentcube_session=<session-id>; Path=/; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict\n323: ```\n324: \n325: **Header-based (alternative):**\n326: ```\n327: X-AgentCube-Session: <session-id>\n328: ```\n329: \n330: **JWT Payload (optional, for auth integration):**\n331: ```json\n332: {\n333:   \"sub\": \"user-123\",\n334:   \"sid\": \"session-abc\",\n335:   \"nss\": \"default\",\n336:   \"bk\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n337:   \"bkn\": \"my-runtime\",\n338:   \"iat\": 1699000000,\n339:   \"exp\": 1699086400\n340: }\n341: ```\n342: \n343: ### Session Endpoints\n344: \n345: The router exposes management endpoints for session operations:\n346: \n347: ```\n348: GET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n349:        - List all active sessions\n350:        - Query params: namespace, kind, userId\n351: \n352: GET    /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n353:        - Get session details\n354: \n355: DELETE /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions/{id}\n356:        - Terminate a session\n357: \n358: POST   /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/sessions\n359:        - Create a new session (explicit)\n360:        - Body: { \"namespace\", \"kind\", \"backendName\", \"userId\" }\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ### Session Management Interface\n364: \n365: ```go\n366: type SessionManagerInterface interface {\n367:     // CreateSession creates a new session\n368:     CreateSession(ctx context.Context, req *CreateSessionRequest) (*Session, error)\n369:     \n370:     // GetSession retrieves a session by ID\n371:     GetSession(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error)\n372:     \n373:     // UpdateSession updates session metadata\n374:     UpdateSession(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error\n375:     \n376:     // DeleteSession terminates and removes a session\n377:     DeleteSession(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n378:     \n379:     // ListSessions returns sessions matching filters\n380:     ListSessions(ctx context.Context, filters *SessionFilters) ([]*Session, error)\n381:     \n382:     // CleanupExpiredSessions removes expired sessions\n383:     CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n384:     \n385:     // Start starts the session manager background tasks\n386:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n387:     \n388:     // Shutdown gracefully stops the session manager\n389:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n390: }\n391: \n392: type CreateSessionRequest struct {\n393:     Namespace   string\n394:     Kind        string\n395:     BackendName string\n396:     BackendURL  string\n397:     UserID      string\n398:     Metadata    map[string]string\n399: }\n400: \n401: type SessionFilters struct {\n402:     Namespace string\n403:     Kind      string\n404:     UserID    string\n405:     State     SessionState\n406: }\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### Resolve with Session Affinity\n410: \n411: **Modified Resolve Operation:**\n412: \n413: ```go\n414: // ResolveWithSession resolves route considering session affinity\n415: func (r *Resolver) ResolveWithSession(\n416:     ctx context.Context,\n417:     req *http.Request,\n418:     session *Session,\n419: ) (*RouteEntry, error)\n420: ```\n421: \n422: **Behavior:**\n423: 1. If session exists and is bound to a backend → return that backend\n424: 2. If session exists but backend is unhealthy → reassign to healthy backend\n425: 3. If no session → select backend using load balancing strategy\n426: 4. Update session's LastActivityAt timestamp\n427: \n428: ## Error Handling\n429: \n430: ### Error Types\n431: \n432: ```go\n433: var (\n434:     // Session errors\n435:     ErrSessionNotFound      = errors.New(\"session not found\")\n436:     ErrSessionExpired       = errors.New(\"session has expired\")\n437:     ErrSessionTerminated    = errors.New(\"session was terminated\")\n438:     ErrSessionCreateFailed  = errors.New(\"failed to create session\")\n439:     ErrSessionStoreError    = errors.New(\"session store error\")\n440:     \n441:     // Session affinity errors\n442:     ErrBackendUnavailable   = errors.New(\"backend unavailable for session\")\n443:     ErrAffinityBroken       = errors.New(\"session affinity cannot be maintained\")\n444:     \n445:     // Configuration errors\n446:     ErrInvalidSessionConfig = errors.New(\"invalid session configuration\")\n447:     ErrRedisConnectionFailed = errors.New(\"failed to connect to redis\")\n448: )\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Error Response Format\n452: \n453: ```go\n454: type SessionErrorResponse struct {\n455:     Error       string            `json:\"error\"`\n456:     Code        string            `json:\"code\"`\n457:     SessionID   string            `json:\"sessionId,omitempty\"`\n458:     Details     map[string]string `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n459:     Timestamp   string            `json:\"timestamp\"`\n460: }\n461: \n462: // Error codes\n463: const (\n464:     ErrCodeSessionNotFound      = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n465:     ErrCodeSessionExpired       = \"SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n466:     ErrCodeSessionTerminated    = \"SESSION_TERMINATED\"\n467:     ErrCodeBackendUnavailable   = \"BACKEND_UNAVAILABLE\"\n468:     ErrCodeAffinityBroken       = \"AFFINITY_BROKEN\"\n469: )\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ### Session Recovery Strategy\n473: \n474: | Scenario | Action |\n475: |----------|--------|\n476: | Session not found | Create new session, return 201 |\n477: | Session expired | Clean up, create new session |\n478: | Backend unhealthy | Reassign to healthy backend (if allowed) |\n479: | Redis connection lost | Fall back to memory store (if configured) |\n480: | Session store error | Log error, continue with degraded mode |\n481: \n482: ### Graceful Degradation\n483: \n484: ```go\n485: type FallbackStrategy string\n486: \n487: const (\n488:     FallbackMemory FallbackStrategy = \"memory\" // Use in-memory store\n489:     FallbackDirect FallbackStrategy = \"direct\" // Direct routing without sessions\n490:     FallbackReject FallbackStrategy = \"reject\" // Reject requests\n491: )\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ## Testing Strategy\n495: \n496: ### Unit Tests\n497: \n498: **File**: `session/manager_test.go`\n499: \n500: ```go\n501: func TestSessionManager_CreateSession(t *testing.T)\n502: func TestSessionManager_GetSession(t *testing.T)\n503: func TestSessionManager_DeleteSession(t *testing.T)\n504: func TestSessionManager_ListSessions(t *testing.T)\n505: func TestSessionManager_CleanupExpiredSessions(t *testing.T)\n506: func TestSessionManager_SessionAffinity(t *testing.T)\n507: func TestSessionManager_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n508: ```\n509: \n510: **File**: `session/session_test.go`\n511: \n512: ```go\n513: func TestSession_IsExpired(t *testing.T)\n514: func TestSession_IsIdle(t *testing.T)\n515: func TestSession_UpdateActivity(t *testing.T)\n516: func TestSession_MarshalJSON(t *testing.T)\n517: func TestSession_ThreadSafety(t *testing.T)\n518: ```\n519: \n520: **File**: `session/redis_store_test.go`\n521: \n522: ```go\n523: func TestRedisStore_GetSet(t *testing.T)\n524: func TestRedisStore_Delete(t *testing.T)\n525: func TestRedisStore_List(t *testing.T)\n526: func TestRedisStore_ListByUser(t *testing.T)\n527: func TestRedisStore_ConnectionFailure(t *testing.T)\n528: func TestRedisStore_KeyExpiration(t *testing.T)\n529: ```\n530: \n531: **File**: `session/memory_store_test.go`\n532: \n533: ```go\n534: func TestMemoryStore_BasicOperations(t *testing.T)\n535: func TestMemoryStore_ListFiltering(t *testing.T)\n536: func TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T)\n537: func TestMemoryStore_MemoryLimit(t *testing.T)\n538: ```\n539: \n540: **File**: `middleware/session_middleware_test.go`\n541: \n542: ```go\n543: func TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Cookie(t *testing.T)\n544: func TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Header(t *testing.T)\n545: func TestSessionMiddleware_AttachSession(t *testing.T)\n546: func TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_Success(t *testing.T)\n547: func TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_InvalidToken(t *testing.T)\n548: ```\n549: \n550: ### Test Fixtures\n551: \n552: ```go\n553: func newTestSession(id, namespace, backendName, userID string) *Session {\n554:     return &Session{\n555:         ID:             id,\n556:         Namespace:      namespace,\n557:         Kind:           \"AgentRuntime\",\n558:         BackendName:    backendName,\n559:         BackendURL:     \"http://backend:8080\",\n560:         UserID:         userID,\n561:         CreatedAt:      time.Now(),\n562:         LastActivityAt: time.Now(),\n563:         ExpiresAt:      time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n564:         State:          SessionStateActive,\n565:     }\n566: }\n567: \n568: func newTestSessionConfig() *SessionConfig {\n569:     return &SessionConfig{\n570:         Enabled:         true,\n571:         CookieName:      \"agentcube_session\",\n572:         TokenHeader:     \"X-AgentCube-Session\",\n573:         MaxDuration:     8 * time.Hour,\n574:         IdleTimeout:     15 * time.Minute,\n575:         CleanupInterval: 1 * time.Minute,\n576:         StoreType:       \"memory\",\n577:     }\n578: }\n579: \n580: func newTestRedisConfig(addr, password string) *RedisSessionConfig {\n581:     return &RedisSessionConfig{\n582:         Addr:         addr,\n583:         Password:     password,\n584:         DB:           0,\n585:         KeyPrefix:    \"agentcube:session:\",\n586:         PoolSize:     10,\n587:         DialTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n588:         ReadTimeout:  3 * time.Second,\n589:         WriteTimeout: 3 * time.Second,\n590:     }\n591: }\n592: ```\n593: \n594: ### Mock Setup\n595: \n596: ```go\n597: // Mock session store for testing\n598: type MockSessionStore struct {\n599:     sessions sync.Map\n600:     mu       sync.Mutex\n601: }\n602: \n603: func (m *MockSessionStore) Get(ctx context.Context, id string) (*Session, error) {\n604:     if v, ok := m.sessions.Load(id); ok {\n605:         return v.(*Session), nil\n606:     }\n607:     return nil, ErrSessionNotFound\n608: }\n609: \n610: func (m *MockSessionStore) Set(ctx context.Context, session *Session) error {\n611:     m.sessions.Store(session.ID, session)\n612:     return nil\n613: }\n614: \n615: // Mock Redis server for integration tests\n616: func newMockRedisServer() *miniredis.Miniredis {\n617:     mr, _ := miniredis.Run()\n618:     return mr\n619: }\n620: ```\n621: \n622: ### Integration Tests\n623: \n624: **File**: `session/session_integration_test.go`\n625: \n626: ```go\n627: // Test scenarios (requires Redis):\n628: func TestSessionManager_RedisPersistence(t *testing.T)\n629: func TestSessionManager_SessionExpiration(t *testing.T)\n630: func TestSessionManager_ConcurrentSessionAccess(t *testing.T)\n631: func TestSessionManager_CleanupRoutine(t *testing.T)\n632: func TestSessionManager_Failover(t *testing.T)\n633: ```\n634: \n635: ### Performance Tests\n636: \n637: ```go\n638: func BenchmarkSessionManager_CreateSession(b *testing.B)\n639: func BenchmarkSessionManager_GetSession(b *testing.B)\n640: func BenchmarkSessionStore_Redis(b *testing.B)\n641: func BenchmarkSessionStore_Memory(b *testing.B)\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ### Coverage Requirements\n645: \n646: - Session manager: 100%\n647: - Session store implementations: 100%\n648: - Middleware: 100%\n649: - Error handling paths: 100%\n650: - Overall: ≥85%\n651: \n652: ## Implementation Notes\n653: \n654: ### Session ID Generation\n655: \n656: ```go\n657: func GenerateSessionID() string {\n658:     // Format: sess_<timestamp>_<random>\n659:     // Example: sess_1699000000_abc123def456\n660:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"sess_%d_%s\", \n661:         time.Now().UnixNano(),\n662:         base64.RawURLEncoding.EncodeToString(randomBytes(16)),\n663:     )\n664: }\n665: ```\n666: \n667: ### Redis Key Schema\n668: \n669: ```\n670: # Session data (with TTL)\n671: agentcube:session:{session-id} = JSON(session)\n672: \n673: # User session index (Set)\n674: agentcube:user:{user-id}:sessions = {session-id-1, session-id-2, ...}\n675: \n676: # Backend session index (Set)\n677: agentcube:backend:{namespace}:{kind}:{name}:sessions = {session-id-1, ...}\n678: \n679: # Active sessions counter\n680: agentcube:stats:active_sessions = {count}\n681: ```\n682: \n683: ### Session Cleanup Strategy\n684: \n685: ```go\n686: // Background cleanup routine\n687: func (m *SessionManager) cleanupLoop(ctx context.Context) {\n688:     ticker := time.NewTicker(m.config.CleanupInterval)\n689:     defer ticker.Stop()\n690:     \n691:     for {\n692:         select {\n693:         case <-ctx.Done():\n694:             return\n695:         case <-ticker.C:\n696:             expired, err := m.CleanupExpiredSessions(ctx)\n697:             if err != nil {\n698:                 m.metrics.ErrorsTotal.Inc()\n699:             }\n700:             m.metrics.SessionsExpired.Add(float64(expired))\n701:         }\n702:     }\n703: }\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ### Session Affinity Algorithm\n707: \n708: ```go\n709: func (r *Resolver) resolveWithAffinity(\n710:     session *Session,\n711:     availableBackends []*RouteEntry,\n712: ) (*RouteEntry, error) {\n713:     // Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n714:     if session != nil {\n715:         for _, backend := range availableBackends {\n716:             if backend.Name == session.BackendName && backend.Health.Healthy {\n717:                 return backend, nil\n718:             }\n719:         }\n720:         // Current backend unhealthy - need to reassign\n721:     }\n722:     \n723:     // Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n724:     return selectLeastLoaded(availableBackends), nil\n725: }\n726: ```\n727: \n728: ### Connection Pool Configuration\n729: \n730: ```go\n731: func NewRedisPool(config *RedisSessionConfig) *redis.Client {\n732:     return redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n733:         Addr:         config.Addr,\n734:         Password:     config.Password,\n735:         DB:           config.DB,\n736:         PoolSize:     config.PoolSize,\n737:         MinIdleConns: config.PoolSize / 2,\n738:         MaxConnAge:   24 * time.Hour,\n739:         DialTimeout:  config.DialTimeout,\n740:         ReadTimeout:  config.ReadTimeout,\n741:         WriteTimeout: config.WriteTimeout,\n742:         OnConnect: func(ctx context.Context, cn *redis.Conn) error {\n743:             log.Printf(\"Redis connection established: %v\", cn)\n744:             return nil\n745:         },\n746:     })\n747: }\n748: ```\n749: \n750: ### Graceful Shutdown\n751: \n752: ```go\n753: func (m *SessionManager) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n754:     // 1. Stop cleanup loop\n755:     close(m.stopCh)\n756:     \n757:     // 2. Wait for background tasks\n758:     done := make(chan struct{})\n759:     go func() {\n760:         m.wg.Wait()\n761:         close(done)\n762:     }()\n763:     \n764:     select {\n765:     case <-done:\n766:         // Cleanup completed\n767:     case <-ctx.Done():\n768:         return ctx.Err()\n769:     case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n770:         return errors.New(\"shutdown timeout\")\n771:     }\n772:     \n773:     // 3. Persist in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n774:     if ms, ok := m.store.(*MemoryStore); ok {\n775:         if err := ms.Persist(ctx); err != nil {\n776:             log.Printf(\"Failed to persist sessions: %v\", err)\n777:         }\n778:     }\n779:     \n780:     // 4. Close store connection\n781:     return m.store.Close()\n782: }\n783: ```\n784: \n785: ### Metrics Exposure\n786: \n787: ```go\n788: // Prometheus metrics\n789: func (m *SessionManager) RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) {\n790:     m.metrics.ActiveSessions = prometheus.NewGauge(prometheus.GaugeOpts{\n791:         Name: \"agentcube_router_active_sessions\",\n792:         Help: \"Number of active sessions\",\n793:     })\n794:     \n795:     m.metrics.SessionsCreated = prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n796:         Name: \"agentcube_router_sessions_created_total\",\n797:         Help: \"Total number of sessions created\",\n798:     })\n799:     \n800:     m.metrics.SessionDuration = prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n801:         Name:    \"agentcube_router_session_duration_seconds\",\n802:         Help:    \"Session duration in seconds\",\n803:         Buckets: prometheus.ExponentialBuckets(60, 2, 10),\n804:     })\n805:     \n806:     reg.MustRegister(\n807:         m.metrics.ActiveSessions,\n808:         m.metrics.SessionsCreated,\n809:         m.metrics.SessionsExpired,\n810:         m.metrics.SessionsTerminated,\n811:         m.metrics.SessionDuration,\n812:         m.metrics.StoreLatency,\n813:     )\n814: }\n815: ```\n816: \n817: ### Configuration Example\n818: \n819: ```yaml\n820: # Helm values.yaml\n821: router:\n822:   session:\n823:     enabled: true\n824:     cookieName: agentcube_session\n825:     maxDuration: 8h\n826:     idleTimeout: 15m\n827:     cleanupInterval: 1m\n828:     store:\n829:       type: redis\n830:       redis:\n831:         addr: redis.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:6379\n832:         password: \"\"\n833:         db: 0\n834:         keyPrefix: \"agentcube:session:\"\n835:         poolSize: 10\n836: ```\n837: \n838: ### Environment Variables\n839: \n840: ```bash\n841: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_ENABLED=true\n842: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_COOKIE_NAME=agentcube_session\n843: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_MAX_DURATION=8h\n844: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_IDLE_TIMEOUT=15m\n845: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_CLEANUP_INTERVAL=1m\n846: AGENTCUBE_SESSION_STORE_TYPE=redis\n847: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379\n848: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_PASSWORD=\n849: AGENTCUBE_REDIS_DB=0\n850: ```\n\n(End of file - total 850 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-010 — Router Session Management\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for session management capabilities within the Router module (`pkg/router`). The session management feature enables the router to track, manage, and enforce lifecycle policies for user sessions connecting to AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter backends.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Session Creation**: Create a new session when a client makes the first request to a backend\n2. **Session Tracking**: Track active sessions per backend (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)\n3. **Session Binding**: Bind client requests to specific backend instances based on session affinity\n4. **Session Timeout**: Enforce session timeout policies (idle timeout, max duration)\n5. **Session Cleanup**: Clean up expired or abandoned sessions\n6. **Session Metrics**: Expose metrics for active sessions, session creation rate, etc.\n\n### Non-Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Performance**: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md","time":{"start":1775849592338,"end":1775849592376}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849592381,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e23982001hHpXlYMkQsPIpC","messageID":"msg_d78e226b70010vezKKvbv5256s","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_65f6adeb702642cbb4934f4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-009 Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Router module (`pkg/router`) that acts as an HTTP reverse proxy, routing incoming requests to appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter backends based on Kubernetes CRD resources.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/router/\n13: ├── router.go                   # Main router implementation\n14: ├── router_test.go             # Unit tests\n15: ├── handler.go                 # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n16: ├── handler_test.go            # Handler tests\n17: ├── resolver.go                # Route resolution logic\n18: ├── resolver_test.go           # Resolver tests\n19: ├── health.go                  # Health check manager\n20: ├── health_test.go             # Health check tests\n21: ├── config.go                  # Configuration structures\n22: └── types.go                   # Type definitions\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### Integration Points\n26: \n27: - **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n28: - **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources via `SharedInformerFactory`\n29: - **Listers**: Provides cached read access for route resolution\n30: - **HTTP Client**: Reusable connection pool for backend requests\n31: \n32: ### High-Level Flow\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n36: │   Client    │────▶│   Handler    │────▶│  Resolver   │────▶│  RouteEntry     │\n37: │             │     │              │     │             │     │  (from routes)  │\n38: └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n39:                            │                                          │\n40:                            ▼                                          ▼\n41:                     ┌──────────────┐                          ┌─────────────────┐\n42:                     │   Router     │                          │  Backend URL    │\n43:                     │  (manages    │                          │  (proxy target) │\n44:                     │   routes)    │                          │                 │\n45:                     └──────────────┘                          └─────────────────┘\n46:                            │\n47:                            ▼\n48:                     ┌──────────────┐\n49:                     │  Informers   │\n50:                     │  (watch CRs) │\n51:                     └──────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ## Data Structures\n55: \n56: ### Router\n57: \n58: ```go\n59: type Router struct {\n60:     config          *RouterConfig\n61:     routes          sync.Map // map[string]*RouteEntry\n62:     httpClient      *http.Client\n63:     kubeClient      *versioned.Clientset\n64:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n65:     runtimeInformer v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\n66:     interpreterInformer v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n67:     stopCh          chan struct{}\n68:     wg              sync.WaitGroup\n69:     mu              sync.RWMutex\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### RouterConfig\n74: \n75: ```go\n76: type RouterConfig struct {\n77:     KubeConfig          *rest.Config\n78:     ListenAddr          string\n79:     ReadTimeout         time.Duration\n80:     WriteTimeout        time.Duration\n81:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n82:     MaxConnsPerHost     int\n83:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n84:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n85:     UnhealthyThreshold  int\n86:     Namespace           string // empty means all namespaces\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### RouteEntry\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type RouteEntry struct {\n94:     Name       string\n95:     Namespace  string\n96:     Kind       string // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n97:     BackendURL string\n98:     Health     HealthStatus\n99:     UpdatedAt  time.Time\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### HealthStatus\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type HealthStatus struct {\n107:     Healthy             bool\n108:     LastCheck           time.Time\n109:     Error               error\n110:     ConsecutiveFailures int\n111:     mu                  sync.Mutex\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### RouteKey\n116: \n117: ```go\n118: // routeKey generates unique key for route storage\n119: func routeKey(namespace, kind, name string) string {\n120:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s\", namespace, kind, name)\n121: }\n122: ```\n123: \n124: ## API Contracts\n125: \n126: ### Incoming Request Format\n127: \n128: **Path Pattern:**\n129: ```\n130: /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/{resourceType}/{name}[/{subpath}]\n131: ```\n132: \n133: **Resource Types:**\n134: - `agentruntimes` → Maps to AgentRuntime CR\n135: - `codeinterpreters` → Maps to CodeInterpreter CR\n136: \n137: **Headers (added by router):**\n138: - `X-Forwarded-For`: Client IP\n139: - `X-Real-IP`: Client IP\n140: - `X-Forwarded-Host`: Original host\n141: - `X-Forwarded-Proto`: Request scheme\n142: \n143: ### Processor Interface\n144: \n145: ```go\n146: type RouterInterface interface {\n147:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n148:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n149:     ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Resolve Operation\n154: \n155: **Input**: `*http.Request`\n156: \n157: **Output**: `*RouteEntry` or error\n158: \n159: **Behavior**:\n160: 1. Parse namespace, resourceType, name from path\n161: 2. Look up route from `routes` sync.Map\n162: 3. Check backend health status\n163: 4. Return RouteEntry or error\n164: \n165: ### Proxy Operation\n166: \n167: **Input**: `http.ResponseWriter`, `*http.Request`, `*RouteEntry`\n168: \n169: **Output**: error\n170: \n171: **Behavior**:\n172: 1. Build backend URL from RouteEntry.BackendURL\n173: 2. Clone request with new context\n174: 3. Add forwarding headers\n175: 4. Execute request via `httpClient.Do()`\n176: 5. Copy response headers and body\n177: 6. Handle errors appropriately\n178: \n179: ## Error Handling\n180: \n181: ### Error Types\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: var (\n185:     ErrRouteNotFound      = errors.New(\"route not found\")\n186:     ErrNoHealthyBackends  = errors.New(\"no healthy backends available\")\n187:     ErrInvalidResourceType = errors.New(\"invalid resource type\")\n188:     ErrMalformedPath      = errors.New(\"malformed request path\")\n189: )\n190: \n191: var (\n192:     ErrBackendConnection  = errors.New(\"failed to connect to backend\")\n193:     ErrBackendTimeout     = errors.New(\"backend timeout\")\n194:     ErrBackendUnavailable = errors.New(\"backend unavailable\")\n195: )\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### Error Response Format\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: type ErrorResponse struct {\n202:     Error       string `json:\"error\"`\n203:     Code        string `json:\"code\"`\n204:     RouteName   string `json:\"routeName,omitempty\"`\n205:     Timestamp   string `json:\"timestamp\"`\n206: }\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### HTTP Status Codes\n210: \n211: | Scenario | Status Code |\n212: |----------|-------------|\n213: | Route not found | 404 |\n214: | Invalid resource type | 400 |\n215: | Malformed path | 400 |\n216: | Backend unavailable | 502 |\n217: | No healthy backends | 503 |\n218: | Backend timeout | 504 |\n219: \n220: ### Retry Strategy\n221: \n222: - **Connection errors**: Retry with next healthy backend (max 2 retries)\n223: - **Timeout**: Mark backend unhealthy, return 504\n224: - **Permanent errors** (4xx from backend): Return immediately\n225: \n226: ### Health Check Failure Policy\n227: \n228: ```\n229: Consecutive Failures → Action\n230: 3                   → Mark unhealthy, remove from rotation\n231: 1                   → Continue serving, log warning\n232: Recovery (1 success) → Mark healthy, restore to rotation\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ## Testing Strategy\n236: \n237: ### Unit Tests\n238: \n239: **File**: `router/router_test.go`\n240: \n241: ```go\n242: // Test cases:\n243: func TestRouter_Start(t *testing.T)\n244: func TestRouter_Shutdown(t *testing.T)\n245: func TestRouter_ServeHTTP(t *testing.T)\n246: func TestRouter_routeKey(t *testing.T)\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **File**: `router/resolver_test.go`\n250: \n251: ```go\n252: // Test cases:\n253: func TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Success(t *testing.T)\n254: func TestResolver_ResolveRoute_NotFound(t *testing.T)\n255: func TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Unhealthy(t *testing.T)\n256: func TestResolver_ParsePath(t *testing.T)\n257: ```\n258: \n259: **File**: `router/health_test.go`\n260: \n261: ```go\n262: // Test cases:\n263: func TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Success(t *testing.T)\n264: func TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Failure(t *testing.T)\n265: func TestHealthChecker_MarkUnhealthy(t *testing.T)\n266: func TestHealthChecker_MarkHealthy(t *testing.T)\n267: ```\n268: \n269: **File**: `router/handler_test.go`\n270: \n271: ```go\n272: // Test cases:\n273: func TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Success(t *testing.T)\n274: func TestHandler_ProxyRequest_BackendError(t *testing.T)\n275: func TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Timeout(t *testing.T)\n276: func TestHandler_AddForwardingHeaders(t *testing.T)\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ### Test Fixtures\n280: \n281: ```go\n282: func newTestRouteEntry(name, namespace, backendURL string) *RouteEntry {\n283:     return &RouteEntry{\n284:         Name:       name,\n285:         Namespace:  namespace,\n286:         Kind:       \"AgentRuntime\",\n287:         BackendURL: backendURL,\n288:         Health:     HealthStatus{Healthy: true},\n289:         UpdatedAt:  time.Now(),\n290:     }\n291: }\n292: \n293: func newTestRouterConfig() *RouterConfig {\n294:     return &RouterConfig{\n295:         ListenAddr:          \":8080\",\n296:         ReadTimeout:         15 * time.Second,\n297:         WriteTimeout:        30 * time.Second,\n298:         IdleTimeout:         60 * time.Second,\n299:         HealthCheckInterval: 10 * time.Second,\n300:         HealthCheckTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n301:         UnhealthyThreshold:  3,\n302:     }\n303: }\n304: ```\n305: \n306: ### Mock Setup\n307: \n308: ```go\n309: // Fake kube client for testing\n310: func newFakeKubeClient(objects ...runtime.Object) *versioned.Clientset {\n311:     return fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)\n312: }\n313: \n314: // Mock backend server\n315: func newMockBackend(handler http.HandlerFunc) *httptest.Server {\n316:     return httptest.NewServer(handler)\n317: }\n318: ```\n319: \n320: ### Integration Tests\n321: \n322: **File**: `router/router_integration_test.go`\n323: \n324: ```go\n325: // Test scenarios (requires kind cluster):\n326: // 1. CRD creation triggers route addition\n327: // 2. CRD deletion triggers route removal\n328: // 3. End-to-end request routing\n329: // 4. Health check removes unhealthy backend\n330: // 5. Concurrent request handling\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### Coverage Requirements\n334: \n335: - Route resolution: 100%\n336: - Proxy handler: 100%\n337: - Health check: 100%\n338: - Error handling paths: 100%\n339: - Overall: ≥85%\n340: \n341: ## Implementation Notes\n342: \n343: ### Route Key Format\n344: \n345: Routes stored in sync.Map with key: `{namespace}/{kind}/{name}`\n346: - Kind is lowercased: `agentruntime` or `codeinterpreter`\n347: \n348: ### Labels Monitored\n349: \n350: Informer filters resources with labels:\n351: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/expose: \"true\"` (only exposed resources are routed)\n352: \n353: ### Backend URL Discovery\n354: \n355: Backend URL extracted from CR spec:\n356: - AgentRuntime: `.spec.endpoint`\n357: - CodeInterpreter: `.spec.serviceURL`\n358: \n359: ### Connection Pooling\n360: \n361: HTTP client configured with:\n362: ```go\n363: &http.Transport{\n364:     MaxConnsPerHost:     config.MaxConnsPerHost,\n365:     MaxIdleConns:        100,\n366:     MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 10,\n367:     IdleConnTimeout:     90 * time.Second,\n368: }\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ### Graceful Shutdown\n372: \n373: 1. Stop accepting new connections\n374: 2. Close idle connections\n375: 3. Wait for in-flight requests (max 30s)\n376: 4. Stop informers\n377: 5. Close Kubernetes client\n\n(End of file - total 377 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-009 Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Router module (`pkg/router`) that acts as an HTTP reverse proxy, routing incoming requests to appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter backends based on Kubernetes CRD resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── router.go                   # Main router implementation\n├── router_test.go             # Unit tests\n├── handler.go                 # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n├── handler_test.go            # Handler tests\n├── resolver.go                # Route resolution logic\n├── resolver_test.go           # Resolver tests\n├── health.go                  # Health check manager\n├── health_test.go             # Health check tests","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md","time":{"start":1775849592341,"end":1775849592380}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849592383,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e243ea001R7mXakG5z0siEy","messageID":"msg_d78e226b70010vezKKvbv5256s","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_30057f9a7214438aa0e252c2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Type Definitions\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/types.go`\n20:   - Define `RouteEntry` struct with fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `Kind`, `BackendURL`, `Health`, `UpdatedAt`\n21:   - Define `HealthStatus` struct with fields: `Healthy`, `LastCheck`, `Error`, `ConsecutiveFailures`, `mu`\n22:   - Define `ErrorResponse` struct for error responses\n23:   - Add `routeKey()` helper function\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `pkg/router/config.go`\n26:   - Define `RouterConfig` struct with all configuration fields\n27:   - Implement `DefaultRouterConfig()` function\n28:   - Implement config validation method\n29: \n30: ### Phase 2: Router Core\n31: \n32: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/router/router.go`\n33:   - Define `Router` struct with all required fields\n34:   - Implement `NewRouter()` constructor\n35:   - Implement `NewRouterWithClient()` constructor\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `Router.Start()` method\n38:   - Start informer factory\n39:   - Wait for cache sync\n40:   - Start HTTP server\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Router.Shutdown()` method\n43:   - Stop accepting new connections\n44:   - Wait for in-flight requests (max 30s)\n45:   - Shutdown informers\n46:   - Release resources\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Router.ServeHTTP()` method\n49:   - Delegate to handler\n50: \n51: ### Phase 3: Route Resolver\n52: \n53: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/resolver.go`\n54:   - Implement `Resolve()` method to lookup routes from sync.Map\n55:   - Implement `parsePath()` to extract namespace, resourceType, name from URL path\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement informer event handlers\n58:   - `onAgentRuntimeAdd()` - add route on CR creation\n59:   - `onAgentRuntimeUpdate()` - update route on CR update\n60:   - `onAgentRuntimeDelete()` - remove route on CR deletion\n61:   - `onCodeInterpreterAdd/Update/Delete()` - same for CodeInterpreter\n62: \n63: ### Phase 4: HTTP Handler\n64: \n65: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/handler.go`\n66:   - Define `Handler` struct\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `Handler.ProxyRequest()` method\n69:   - Build backend URL from RouteEntry\n70:   - Clone request with new context\n71:   - Add forwarding headers (X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP, X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Proto)\n72:   - Execute request via httpClient.Do()\n73:   - Copy response headers and body\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Handler.writeErrorResponse()` method\n76:   - Write JSON error response with appropriate status code\n77: \n78: ### Phase 5: Health Check Manager\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/health.go`\n81:   - Define `HealthChecker` struct\n82: \n83: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `HealthChecker.Start()` method\n84:   - Periodic health check loop\n85:   - Check backend health at configured interval\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `HealthChecker.CheckHealth()` method\n88:   - HTTP GET to backend health endpoint\n89:   - Update HealthStatus based on response\n90:   - Apply health check failure policy (3 failures → mark unhealthy)\n91: \n92: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `HealthChecker.MarkUnhealthy()` and `HealthChecker.MarkHealthy()` methods\n93: \n94: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `/healthz` HTTP handler\n95:   - Check informer sync status\n96:   - Return HTTP 200/503 based on health\n97: \n98: ### Phase 6: Error Handling\n99: \n100: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Define error types in `pkg/router/errors.go`\n101:   - `ErrRouteNotFound`, `ErrNoHealthyBackends`, `ErrInvalidResourceType`, `ErrMalformedPath`\n102:   - `ErrBackendConnection`, `ErrBackendTimeout`, `ErrBackendUnavailable`\n103: \n104: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement error-to-HTTP-status mapping\n105: \n106: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (TDD)\n107: \n108: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/router/router_test.go`\n109:   - `TestRouter_Start`\n110:   - `TestRouter_Shutdown`\n111:   - `TestRouter_routeKey`\n112: \n113: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `pkg/router/resolver_test.go`\n114:   - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Success`\n115:   - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_NotFound`\n116:   - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Unhealthy`\n117:   - `TestResolver_ParsePath`\n118: \n119: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `pkg/router/health_test.go`\n120:   - `TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Success`\n121:   - `TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Failure`\n122:   - `TestHealthChecker_MarkUnhealthy`\n123:   - `TestHealthChecker_MarkHealthy`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `pkg/router/handler_test.go`\n126:   - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Success`\n127:   - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_BackendError`\n128:   - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Timeout`\n129:   - `TestHandler_AddForwardingHeaders`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `pkg/router/config_test.go`\n132:   - `TestDefaultRouterConfig`\n133:   - `TestRouterConfig_Validate`\n134: \n135: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `pkg/router/router_integration_test.go`\n138:   - Test CRD creation triggers route addition\n139:   - Test CRD deletion triggers route removal\n140:   - End-to-end request routing\n141:   - Health check removes unhealthy backend\n142:   - Concurrent request handling\n143: \n144: ### Phase 9: Documentation\n145: \n146: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/doc.go`\n147: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n148: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Verify `pkg/router/design.md` is complete\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Acceptance Criteria\n153: \n154: - [ ] Router initializes with Kubernetes clientset and informers\n155: - [ ] HTTP requests are routed to correct backend based on CRD resources\n156: - [ ] Informer watches update routes on CRD create/update/delete\n157: - [ ] Namespace-based routing works correctly\n158: - [ ] `/healthz` endpoint returns accurate health status\n159: - [ ] Connection pooling configured with timeouts\n160: - [ ] Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes\n161: - [ ] Graceful shutdown waits for in-flight requests\n162: - [ ] All unit tests pass with ≥85% coverage\n163: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real CRDs\n164: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Dependencies\n169: \n170: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n171: |------------|--------|-------|\n172: | `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes API client |\n173: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | External | Resource types |\n174: | `net/http/httputil` | Go stdlib | Reverse proxy |\n175: | `go.uber.org/zap` | External | Structured logging |\n176: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | External | Metrics (optional) |\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Implementation Order\n181: \n182: ```\n183: TASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013\n184:                               ↓\n185: TASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-030 → TASK-031 → TASK-032\n186:                               ↓\n187: TASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → TASK-044\n188:                               ↓\n189: TASK-050 → TASK-051\n190:                               ↓\n191: TEST-001 → TEST-002 → TEST-003 → TEST-004 → TEST-005 → TEST-010\n192:                               ↓\n193: DOC-001 → DOC-002 → DOC-003\n194: ```\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Type Definitions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/types.go`\n  - Define `RouteEntry` struct with fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `Kind`, `BackendURL`, `Health`, `UpdatedAt`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849592346,"end":1775849592382}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849592385,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e23e61001i5EBYx5E12cc0Q","messageID":"msg_d78e226b70010vezKKvbv5256s","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ecbd8a37e27540b790c97324","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/router  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Implement session management functionality for the pkg/router module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Design session management architecture\n15: - [ ] Implement session storage interface\n16: - [ ] Implement session lifecycle management\n17: - [ ] Add session routing logic\n18: - [ ] Add unit tests\n19: - [ ] Add integration tests\n20: \n21: ## Notes\n22: \n23: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n24: \n25: ## Source Files\n26: \n27: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement session management functionality for the pkg/router module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Design session management architecture\n- [ ] Implement session storage interface\n- [ ] Implement session lifecycle management\n- [ ] Add session routing logic\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/README.md","time":{"start":1775849592344,"end":1775849592384}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849592386,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e2498b001ZWZp5Y2PiB0U6a","messageID":"msg_d78e226b70010vezKKvbv5256s","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d348ba9d6d574fc3874610d7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: \n12: ## Atomic Tasks\n13: \n14: ### Phase 1: GC Policy & Configuration\n15: \n16: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `GCConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go`\n17:   - Fields: `Enabled` (bool), `Interval` (time.Duration), `IdleTimeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleCount` (int), `DryRun` (bool)\n18:   - Document each field with comments\n19: \n20: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultGCConfig()` function\n21:   - Returns default configuration: Enabled=true, Interval=5m, IdleTimeout=30m, MaxIdleCount=100, DryRun=false\n22: \n23: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxState` enum/consts in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/state.go`\n24:   - States: `StateActive`, `StateIdle`, `StateOrphaned`, `StateExpired`\n25:   - Document state transition rules\n26: \n27: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `GCCandidate` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate.go`\n28:   - Fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `State`, `LastActivity` (time.Time), `CreatedAt` (time.Time), `OwnerRef` (string)\n29:   - Methods: `IsExpired()`, `IsIdle()`\n30: \n31: ### Phase 2: GC Core Logic\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `GarbageCollector` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go`\n34:   - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `workloadManager`, `ctx`, `cancel`, `ticker`, `metrics`\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewGarbageCollector()` constructor\n37:   - Takes config, clientset, workloadManager\n38:   - Returns initialized *GarbageCollector\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Start()` method\n41:   - Creates context\n42:   - Starts ticker with configured interval\n43:   - Runs initial GC scan\n44:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n45: \n46: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Stop()` method\n47:   - Cancels context\n48:   - Stops ticker\n49:   - Logs shutdown\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `runGC()` method\n52:   - Scans all sandboxes\n53:   - Evaluates each against GC policy\n54:   - Collects candidates for cleanup\n55:   - Executes cleanup\n56:   - Records metrics\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `scanSandboxes()` method\n59:   - Lists all AgentRuntime sandboxes\n60:   - Lists all CodeInterpreter sandboxes\n61:   - Evaluates state for each\n62:   - Returns list of GCCandidate\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `evaluateState()` method\n65:   - Checks last activity timestamp\n66:   - Checks owner existence\n67:   - Determines sandbox state (Active/Idle/Orphaned/Expired)\n68: \n69: - [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `cleanup()` method\n70:   - Filters candidates by state\n71:   - Respects MaxIdleCount (keeps most recent)\n72:   - Deletes expired/orphaned sandboxes\n73:   - Deletes excess idle sandboxes\n74:   - Returns cleanup summary\n75: \n76: ### Phase 3: Activity Tracking\n77: \n78: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `LastActivityTracker` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity.go`\n79:   - Tracks last activity timestamp per sandbox\n80:   - Fields: `mu` (sync.RWMutex), `activities` (map[string]time.Time)\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `RecordActivity()` method\n83:   - Updates last activity timestamp for sandbox\n84: \n85: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `GetLastActivity()` method\n86:   - Returns last activity timestamp or zero time\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `GetIntegrations()` for activity sources\n89:   - HTTP request middleware integration point\n90:   - Session creation/deletion hooks\n91: \n92: ### Phase 4: Metrics\n93: \n94: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `GCMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go`\n95:   - Fields: `gcRuns` (Counter), `gcDuration` (Histogram), `sandboxesScanned` (Gauge), `sandboxesCleaned` (Counter), `sandboxesByState` (GaugeVec)\n96: \n97: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewGCMetrics()` constructor\n98:   - Creates Prometheus metrics\n99:   - Registers with registerer\n100: \n101: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement metric methods\n102:   - `recordRun(duration time.Duration)`\n103:   - `recordScanned(count int)`\n104:   - `recordCleaned(count int)`\n105:   - `updateStateCounts(stateCounts map[SandboxState]int)`\n106: \n107: ### Phase 5: Configuration Integration\n108: \n109: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Add GC flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n110:   - Flags: `--gc-enabled`, `--gc-interval`, `--gc-idle-timeout`, `--gc-max-idle-count`, `--gc-dry-run`\n111: \n112: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Integrate GC with main startup\n113:   - Load config\n114:   - Create GarbageCollector\n115:   - Start GC as goroutine\n116:   - Register shutdown hook\n117: \n118: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Document environment variables\n119:   - `GC_ENABLED`, `GC_INTERVAL`, `GC_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `GC_MAX_IDLE_COUNT`, `GC_DRY_RUN`\n120: \n121: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n122: \n123: #### Unit Tests - GC Core\n124: \n125: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc_test.go`\n126:   - Given: Configured GC\n127:   - When: Start() then Stop() called\n128:   - Then: GC runs without error, graceful shutdown\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_ExpiredSandboxes`\n131:   - Given: Sandboxes exceeding idle timeout\n132:   - When: runGC() called\n133:   - Then: Expired sandboxes deleted, metrics recorded\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_OrphanedSandboxes`\n136:   - Given: Sandboxes without valid owner\n137:   - When: runGC() called\n138:   - Then: Orphaned sandboxes deleted\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_MaxIdleCount`\n141:   - Given: More idle sandboxes than MaxIdleCount\n142:   - When: runGC() called\n143:   - Then: Oldest idle sandboxes deleted, keeps most recent\n144: \n145: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_DryRun`\n146:   - Given: DryRun=true, expired sandboxes exist\n147:   - When: runGC() called\n148:   - Then: No sandboxes deleted, metrics show what would be cleaned\n149: \n150: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Active`\n151:   - Given: Sandbox with recent activity\n152:   - When: evaluateState() called\n153:   - Then: Returns StateActive\n154: \n155: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Idle`\n156:   - Given: Sandbox with no recent activity but within timeout\n157:   - When: evaluateState() called\n158:   - Then: Returns StateIdle\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Expired`\n161:   - Given: Sandbox exceeding idle timeout\n162:   - When: evaluateState() called\n163:   - Then: Returns StateExpired\n164: \n165: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Orphaned`\n166:   - Given: Sandbox with missing owner\n167:   - When: evaluateState() called\n168:   - Then: Returns StateOrphaned\n169: \n170: #### Unit Tests - Activity Tracker\n171: \n172: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestLastActivityTracker_RecordAndGet` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity_test.go`\n173:   - Given: New tracker\n174:   - When: RecordActivity() then GetLastActivity()\n175:   - Then: Returns recorded timestamp\n176: \n177: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestLastActivityTracker_GetLastActivity_NotFound`\n178:   - Given: New tracker, no activity recorded\n179:   - When: GetLastActivity() called\n180:   - Then: Returns zero time\n181: \n182: #### Unit Tests - GC Candidate\n183: \n184: - [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestGCCandidate_IsExpired` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate_test.go`\n185:   - Given: Candidate with LastActivity exceeding timeout\n186:   - When: IsExpired() called\n187:   - Then: Returns true\n188: \n189: - [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestGCCandidate_IsIdle`\n190:   - Given: Candidate with no recent activity\n191:   - When: IsIdle() called\n192:   - Then: Returns true\n193: \n194: #### Unit Tests - Metrics\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestGCMetrics_RecordRun` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics_test.go`\n197:   - Given: Metrics registered\n198:   - When: recordRun() called\n199:   - Then: Counter and histogram updated\n200: \n201: - [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestGCMetrics_RecordCleaned`\n202:   - Given: Metrics registered\n203:   - When: recordCleaned() called\n204:   - Then: Counter incremented\n205: \n206: #### Test Infrastructure\n207: \n208: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `newTestGC()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc_test.go`\n209:   - Creates fake clientset, config, mock workloadManager\n210:   - Returns initialized GC for testing\n211: \n212: - [ ] **TEST-041**: Create test fixtures\n213:   - `buildAgentRuntime()` - creates test AgentRuntime objects\n214:   - `buildCodeInterpreter()` - creates test CodeInterpreter objects\n215:   - `buildSandboxWithActivity()` - creates sandboxes with specific activity timestamps\n216: \n217: #### Integration Tests\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TEST-050**: `TestGarbageCollector_Integration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/integration_test.go`\n220:   - Use envtest or real K8s cluster\n221:   - Create sandboxes with various states\n222:   - Run GC\n223:   - Verify correct sandboxes cleaned\n224: \n225: - [ ] **TEST-051**: `TestGarbageCollector_PeriodicRun`\n226:   - Start GC with short interval\n227:   - Verify GC runs periodically\n228:   - Verify metrics accumulated\n229: \n230: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n231: \n232: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/doc.go`\n233:   - Package overview\n234:   - GC strategy description\n235:   - Configuration options\n236: \n237: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n238: \n239: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Document GC policy decision logic in code comments\n240:   - State evaluation rules\n241:   - Cleanup priority order\n242: \n243: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md`\n244:   - Add GC section\n245:   - Document configuration options\n246:   - List environment variables\n247: \n248: ## Acceptance Criteria\n249: \n250: - [ ] GC runs periodically at configured interval\n251: - [ ] Expired sandboxes (exceeding idle timeout) are cleaned\n252: - [ ] Orphaned sandboxes (missing owner) are cleaned\n253: - [ ] MaxIdleCount limit enforced (oldest idle sandboxes removed)\n254: - [ ] DryRun mode logs without deleting\n255: - [ ] Activity tracking integrated with HTTP middleware\n256: - [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n257: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n258: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n259: - [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented\n260: - [ ] Configuration via flags and environment variables\n261: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n262: \n263: ## Dependencies\n264: \n265: - **Required**: pkg/workloadmanager base module\n266: - **Required**: Access to K8s clientset for listing/deleting sandboxes\n267: - **Related**: AR-007 (K8s Reconciler) - GC coordinates with reconciler state\n\n(End of file - total 267 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: GC Policy & Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `GCConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go`\n  - Fields: `Enabled` (bool), `Interval` (time.Duration), `IdleTimeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleCount` (int), `DryRun` (bool)\n  - Document each field with comments\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultGCConfig()` function","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849592348,"end":1775849592385}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849592390,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e24f29001q620sEME62oyD5","messageID":"msg_d78e226b70010vezKKvbv5256s","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5b5a90c997764e7590998019","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n18:   - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n19:   - Document each method purpose\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `Request` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n22:   - Fields: `Namespace` (string), `Name` (string)\n23:   - Document usage in reconciliation loop\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `Result` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Requeue` (bool), `RequeueAfter` (time.Duration)\n27:   - Document requeue behavior and priorities\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `ReconcilerConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n30:   - Fields: `ResyncPeriod`, `MaxRetries`, `RateLimitQPS`, `RateLimitBurst`, `ConcurrentReconciles`, `EnableLeaderElection`, `LeaderElectionNamespace`, `LeaderElectionName`\n31:   - All fields documented with comments\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `DefaultReconcilerConfig()` function\n34:   - Returns default configuration per design spec\n35:   - Defaults: ResyncPeriod=10m, MaxRetries=5, RateLimitQPS=10, RateLimitBurst=20, ConcurrentReconciles=2\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define error constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n38:   - Constants: `ErrReconcileFailed`, `ErrPodCreationFailed`, `ErrPodUpdateFailed`, `ErrStatusUpdateFailed`, `ErrOwnerRefFailed`, `ErrCacheMiss`, `ErrInvalidSpec`\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ReconcileError` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n41:   - Fields: `Type` (string), `Message` (string), `Err` (error), `Retryable` (bool)\n42:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-008**: Implement `IsRetryableError()` function\n45:   - Checks `*ReconcileError.Retryable`\n46:   - Checks k8s transient errors: `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests`, `IsServerTimeout`\n47: \n48: ### Phase 2: ControllerManager Infrastructure\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ControllerManager` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n51:   - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `informerFactory`, `reconcilers`, `ctx`, `cancel`\n52:   - Informer fields: `agentRuntimeInformer`, `codeInterpreterInformer`, `podInformer`\n53:   - Lister fields: `agentRuntimeLister`, `codeInterpreterLister`, `podLister`\n54:   - Event recorder: `recorder`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewControllerManager()` constructor\n57:   - Creates versioned clientset and kubernetes clientset\n58:   - Initializes SharedInformerFactory with 10m resync\n59:   - Returns initialized *ControllerManager or error\n60: \n61: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `AddReconciler()` method\n62:   - Appends reconciler to manager's reconcilers slice\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `SetupInformers()` method\n65:   - Gets typed informers from factory\n66:   - Returns error if setup fails\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `StartInformers()` method\n69:   - Starts informer factory\n70:   - Waits for cache sync with timeout\n71:   - Verifies critical informers synced (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod)\n72:   - Gets listers from informers\n73: \n74: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `Start()` method\n75:   - Starts informers\n76:   - Waits for cache sync\n77:   - Starts all reconcilers as goroutines\n78:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n79:   - Handles graceful shutdown (workqueue drain)\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement graceful shutdown in `Start()`\n82:   - Shuts down workqueues\n83:   - Waits for workqueue.Done()\n84:   - Logs shutdown progress\n85: \n86: ### Phase 3: AgentRuntimeReconciler\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `AgentRuntimeReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go`\n89:   - Fields: `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `lister`, `podLister`, `recorder`, `workqueue`, `metrics`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewAgentRuntimeReconciler()` constructor\n92:   - Creates reconciler with rate-limiting workqueue\n93:   - Registers event handlers on AgentRuntime informer\n94:   - Registers event handlers on Pod informer (for owned pods)\n95:   - Returns initialized *AgentRuntimeReconciler\n96: \n97: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `Run()` method for AgentRuntimeReconciler\n98:   - Creates context from stopCh\n99:   - Starts reconciliation workers (ConcurrentReconciles workers)\n100:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n103:   - Fetches AgentRuntime from lister\n104:   - Handles NotFound (skip reconciliation)\n105:   - Handles deletion (calls `reconcileDeletion()`)\n106:   - Reconciles sandbox pod (calls `reconcileSandboxPod()`)\n107:   - Updates status (calls `updateStatus()`)\n108:   - Records events and metrics\n109:   - Returns Result with requeue logic\n110: \n111: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method\n112:   - Handles finalizer cleanup\n113:   - Deletes owned sandbox pod\n114:   - Removes finalizer\n115:   - Returns Result\n116: \n117: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method\n118:   - Checks if pod exists (from lister cache)\n119:   - If not found: builds and creates new pod\n120:   - If exists: checks if update needed\n121:   - If needs update: delete-and-recreate\n122:   - Returns pod or error\n123: \n124: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement event handler methods\n125:   - `enqueueObject(obj interface{})` - casts to AgentRuntime, enqueues Request\n126:   - `enqueueUpdate(old, new interface{})` - handles updates\n127:   - `enqueueDelete(obj interface{})` - handles deletions\n128:   - `enqueueOwnedPod(obj interface{})` - finds owner, enqueues AgentRuntime\n129:   - `enqueueOwnedPodUpdate(old, new interface{})`\n130:   - `enqueueOwnedPodDelete(obj interface{})`\n131: \n132: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterReconciler\n133: \n134: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `CodeInterpreterReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go`\n135:   - Fields: same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCodeInterpreterReconciler()` constructor\n138:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n139:   - Registers event handlers on CodeInterpreter informer\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Run()` method for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n142: \n143: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n144:   - Same reconciliation pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n145:   - Handles CodeInterpreter CRD\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method for CodeInterpreter\n148: \n149: - [ ] **TASK-035**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n150:   - Builds pod from CodeInterpreter spec\n151:   - Same create/update/delete pattern\n152: \n153: - [ ] **TASK-036**: Implement event handler methods for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n154: \n155: ### Phase 5: SandboxProcessor\n156: \n157: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `SandboxProcessor` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor.go`\n158:   - Fields: `k8sClient`, `scheme`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `NewSandboxProcessor()` constructor\n161: \n162: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `BuildSandboxPod()` method for AgentRuntime\n163:   - Creates Pod with name `sandbox-{ar.Name}`\n164:   - Sets labels: `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime`, `agentcube.volcano.sh/type`\n165:   - Builds PodSpec from AgentRuntime spec\n166:   - Sets owner reference\n167:   - Returns *corev1.Pod or error\n168: \n169: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `buildPodSpec()` helper method\n170:   - Builds container spec from `ar.Spec.Container`\n171:   - Sets Resources, Ports, VolumeMounts\n172:   - Sets RestartPolicy=Never\n173:   - Sets SecurityContext, Affinity, Tolerations\n174:   - Adds code interpreter sidecar if enabled\n175: \n176: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `BuildSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n177:   - Similar to AgentRuntime but from CodeInterpreter spec\n178: \n179: - [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `NeedsUpdate()` method\n180:   - Checks if container image changed\n181:   - Checks if resources changed\n182:   - Checks if environment variables changed\n183:   - Returns bool\n184: \n185: - [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `UpdateSandboxPod()` method\n186:   - Deletes existing pod\n187:   - Waits for deletion (using wait.PollUntilContextTimeout)\n188:   - Creates new pod\n189:   - Returns *corev1.Pod or error\n190: \n191: - [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement helper functions\n192:   - `buildEnvFrom()` - converts env vars\n193:   - `buildResourceRequirements()` - converts resource quotas\n194:   - `buildContainerPorts()` - converts network spec\n195:   - `buildVolumeMounts()` and `buildVolumes()`\n196:   - `buildPodSecurityContext()`\n197:   - `buildAffinity()` and `buildTolerations()`\n198:   - `buildCodeInterpreterContainer()` - builds sidecar container\n199: \n200: ### Phase 6: StatusUpdater\n201: \n202: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `StatusUpdater` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater.go`\n203:   - Field: `clientset`\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `NewStatusUpdater()` constructor\n206: \n207: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus()` method\n208:   - Creates deep copy of AgentRuntime\n209:   - Sets Phase based on pod state\n210:   - Sets SandboxRef\n211:   - Builds Conditions from pod\n212:   - Updates Endpoint if pod running\n213:   - Skips update if status unchanged\n214:   - Calls UpdateStatus subresource\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus()` method\n217:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntime\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Implement `mapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase()` function\n220:   - Maps PodPhase to AgentRuntimePhase/CodeInterpreterPhase\n221:   - Handles: Pending, Running, Failed, Succeeded, Unknown\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TASK-055**: Implement `buildConditionsFromPod()` function\n224:   - Converts PodConditions to CRD Conditions\n225: \n226: - [ ] **TASK-056**: Implement `buildEndpointFromPod()` function\n227:   - Builds endpoint URL from PodIP and container port\n228: \n229: ### Phase 7: OwnerReference Management\n230: \n231: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `SetControllerReference()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference.go`\n232:   - Uses `metav1.NewControllerRef()`\n233:   - Sets owner reference on child object\n234: \n235: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `IsOwnedBy()` function\n236:   - Checks if object has owner reference with matching UID and Controller=true\n237: \n238: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `GetControllerOf()` helper\n239:   - Returns controller owner reference if exists\n240: \n241: ### Phase 8: Metrics\n242: \n243: - [ ] **TASK-070**: Implement `ReconcilerMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics.go`\n244:   - Fields: `reconcileDuration` (Histogram), `reconcileErrors` (Counter), `reconcileTotal` (Counter), `workqueueDepth` (Gauge), `workqueueLatency` (Histogram)\n245: \n246: - [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement `NewReconcilerMetrics()` constructor\n247:   - Creates Prometheus metrics with proper naming\n248:   - Registers metrics if registerer provided\n249: \n250: - [ ] **TASK-072**: Implement metric methods\n251:   - `observeReconcileDuration(d time.Duration)`\n252:   - `recordError(errorType string)`\n253:   - `recordReconcile()`\n254: \n255: ### Phase 9: Error Handling & Retry Logic\n256: \n257: - [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement centralized error handling in Reconcile methods\n258:   - Logs errors with context\n259:   - Records metrics\n260:   - Records events\n261:   - Determines retryability\n262: \n263: - [ ] **TASK-081**: Implement `calculateBackoff()` function\n264:   - Exponential backoff: baseDelay * 2^retryCount\n265:   - Max delay: 5 minutes\n266:   - Adds jitter (±20%)\n267: \n268: - [ ] **TASK-082**: Handle k8s error types per design spec\n269:   - `IsNotFound` - skip reconciliation\n270:   - `IsAlreadyExists` - check if update needed\n271:   - `IsConflict` - re-fetch and retry\n272:   - `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests` - exponential backoff\n273: \n274: ### Phase 10: Configuration\n275: \n276: - [ ] **TASK-090**: Add reconciler flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n277:   - Flags: `--reconciler-resync-period`, `--reconciler-max-retries`, `--reconciler-rate-limit-qps`, `--reconciler-rate-limit-burst`, `--reconciler-concurrent`, `--reconciler-leader-election`, `--reconciler-leader-election-namespace`, `--reconciler-leader-election-name`\n278: \n279: - [ ] **TASK-091**: Integrate reconciler with main startup\n280:   - Load config\n281:   - Create ControllerManager\n282:   - Create reconcilers\n283:   - Add reconcilers to manager\n284:   - Start manager\n285: \n286: - [ ] **TASK-092**: Document environment variables\n287:   - `RECONCILER_RESYNC_PERIOD`, `RECONCILER_MAX_RETRIES`, `RECONCILER_RATE_LIMIT_QPS`, `RECONCILER_RATE_LIMIT_BURST`, `RECONCILER_CONCURRENT`, `RECONCILER_LEADER_ELECTION`, etc.\n288: \n289: ### Phase 11: Testing (TDD)\n290: \n291: #### Unit Tests - Reconciler\n292: \n293: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_Success` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler_test.go`\n294:   - Given: AgentRuntime in informer cache\n295:   - When: Reconcile() called\n296:   - Then: Pod created, no error, no requeue\n297:   - Use fake clientset + fake k8s client + mock informers\n298: \n299: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_PodExists`\n300:   - Given: AgentRuntime with existing owned pod\n301:   - When: Reconcile() called\n302:   - Then: No new pod created, status updated\n303: \n304: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_NeedsUpdate`\n305:   - Given: AgentRuntime with changed spec\n306:   - When: Reconcile() called\n307:   - Then: Pod deleted and recreated\n308: \n309: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_Deletion`\n310:   - Given: AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp set\n311:   - When: Reconcile() called\n312:   - Then: Pod deleted, finalizer removed\n313: \n314: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound`\n315:   - Given: Non-existent AgentRuntime\n316:   - When: Reconcile() called\n317:   - Then: No error, no requeue\n318: \n319: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_PodCreationFailed`\n320:   - Given: Invalid pod spec\n321:   - When: Reconcile() called\n322:   - Then: Error returned, event recorded, retry scheduled\n323: \n324: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_StatusUpdateFailed`\n325:   - Given: Pod created but status update fails\n326:   - When: Reconcile() called\n327:   - Then: Error returned, event recorded, retry scheduled\n328: \n329: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Reconcile_Success`\n330:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntime tests\n331: \n332: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Reconcile_WithSidecar`\n333:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with code interpreter enabled\n334:   - When: Reconcile() called\n335:   - Then: Pod created with sidecar container\n336: \n337: #### Unit Tests - SandboxProcessor\n338: \n339: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestSandboxProcessor_BuildSandboxPod` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n340:   - Given: AgentRuntime with full spec\n341:   - When: BuildSandboxPod() called\n342:   - Then: Pod has correct name, labels, owner reference, container spec\n343: \n344: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestSandboxProcessor_BuildSandboxPod_WithCodeInterpreter`\n345:   - Given: AgentRuntime with CodeInterpreter enabled\n346:   - When: BuildSandboxPod() called\n347:   - Then: Pod has sidecar container\n348: \n349: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestSandboxProcessor_NeedsUpdate_ImageChanged`\n350:   - Given: Pod with old image, AgentRuntime with new image\n351:   - When: NeedsUpdate() called\n352:   - Then: Returns true\n353: \n354: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestSandboxProcessor_NeedsUpdate_NoChange`\n355:   - Given: Pod matches AgentRuntime spec\n356:   - When: NeedsUpdate() called\n357:   - Then: Returns false\n358: \n359: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestSandboxProcessor_UpdateSandboxPod`\n360:   - Given: Pod needs update\n361:   - When: UpdateSandboxPod() called\n362:   - Then: Old pod deleted, new pod created\n363: \n364: #### Unit Tests - StatusUpdater\n365: \n366: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodRunning` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater_test.go`\n367:   - Given: AgentRuntime with running pod\n368:   - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n369:   - Then: Status.Phase=Running, SandboxRef set, Endpoint set\n370: \n371: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodPending`\n372:   - Given: AgentRuntime with pending pod\n373:   - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n374:   - Then: Status.Phase=Pending\n375: \n376: - [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_NoChange`\n377:   - Given: Status unchanged\n378:   - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n379:   - Then: No API call made\n380: \n381: - [ ] **TEST-018**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus_PodRunning`\n382:   - Same pattern for CodeInterpreter\n383: \n384: #### Unit Tests - OwnerReference\n385: \n386: - [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestSetControllerReference` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference_test.go`\n387:   - Given: Owner and child objects\n388:   - When: SetControllerReference() called\n389:   - Then: Child has owner reference with Controller=true\n390: \n391: - [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestIsOwnedBy_True`\n392:   - Given: Object with matching owner reference\n393:   - When: IsOwnedBy() called\n394:   - Then: Returns true\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-022**: `TestIsOwnedBy_False`\n397:   - Given: Object with different owner\n398:   - When: IsOwnedBy() called\n399:   - Then: Returns false\n400: \n401: #### Unit Tests - Error Handling\n402: \n403: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestIsRetryableError_True` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors_test.go`\n404:   - Given: Timeout, TooManyRequests errors\n405:   - When: IsRetryableError() called\n406:   - Then: Returns true\n407: \n408: - [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestIsRetryableError_False`\n409:   - Given: NotFound, InvalidSpec errors\n410:   - When: IsRetryableError() called\n411:   - Then: Returns false\n412: \n413: - [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestCalculateBackoff`\n414:   - Given: Various retry counts\n415:   - When: calculateBackoff() called\n416:   - Then: Returns exponentially increasing delays with jitter\n417: \n418: #### Unit Tests - Metrics\n419: \n420: - [ ] **TEST-040**: `TestReconcilerMetrics_ObserveReconcileDuration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics_test.go`\n421:   - Given: Metrics registered\n422:   - When: observeReconcileDuration() called\n423:   - Then: Histogram updated\n424: \n425: - [ ] **TEST-041**: `TestReconcilerMetrics_RecordError`\n426:   - Given: Metrics registered\n427:   - When: recordError() called\n428:   - Then: Counter incremented\n429: \n430: #### Test Infrastructure\n431: \n432: - [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `newTestReconciler()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler_test.go`\n433:   - Creates fake clientset, fake k8s client, informers, recorder\n434:   - Returns initialized reconciler for testing\n435: \n436: - [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `newTestControllerManager()` helper\n437:   - Uses envtest for integration tests\n438:   - Returns ControllerManager with teardown function\n439: \n440: - [ ] **TEST-052**: Create mock implementations\n441:   - Mock Reconciler interface\n442:   - Mock metrics interface\n443: \n444: - [ ] **TEST-053**: Create test fixtures\n445:   - `buildAgentRuntime()` - creates test AgentRuntime objects\n446:   - `buildCodeInterpreter()` - creates test CodeInterpreter objects\n447:   - `buildPod()` - creates test Pod objects\n448:   - `buildPodWithStatus()` - creates pods with specific status\n449: \n450: #### Integration Tests\n451: \n452: - [ ] **TEST-060**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Integration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/integration_test.go`\n453:   - Use envtest to start real K8s API server\n454:   - Create CRD\n455:   - Create AgentRuntime\n456:   - Trigger reconciliation\n457:   - Verify pod created\n458:   - Verify status updated\n459: \n460: - [ ] **TEST-061**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Integration`\n461:   - Same pattern for CodeInterpreter\n462: \n463: - [ ] **TEST-062**: `TestControllerManager_StartStop`\n464:   - Create ControllerManager\n465:   - Start manager\n466:   - Wait for cache sync\n467:   - Stop manager\n468:   - Verify graceful shutdown\n469: \n470: #### Coverage Verification\n471: \n472: - [ ] **TEST-070**: Run coverage check\n473:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n474:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.5\n475:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n476:   - Verify all reconciliation paths covered\n477: \n478: ### Phase 12: Documentation\n479: \n480: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/doc.go`\n481:   - Package overview\n482:   - Architecture description\n483:   - Usage example\n484: \n485: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n486:   - Document parameters, return values\n487:   - Document error conditions\n488:   - Include examples where applicable\n489: \n490: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Document reconciliation loop in code comments\n491:   - Step-by-step flow\n492:   - Error handling strategy\n493:   - Retry behavior\n494: \n495: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md`\n496:   - Add reconciler architecture section\n497:   - Include component diagram\n498:   - Document configuration options\n499:   - List environment variables\n500: \n501: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Add API contracts documentation\n502:   - Reconciliation contract\n503:   - Owner reference pattern\n504:   - Status update contract\n505:   - Event recording\n506: \n507: ## Acceptance Criteria\n508: \n509: - [ ] ControllerManager implemented with proper lifecycle management\n510: - [ ] AgentRuntimeReconciler implemented with full reconciliation loop\n511: - [ ] CodeInterpreterReconciler implemented with full reconciliation loop\n512: - [ ] SandboxProcessor builds pods from both CRD types\n513: - [ ] StatusUpdater updates CRD status based on pod state\n514: - [ ] Owner reference management ensures proper garbage collection\n515: - [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n516: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n517: - [ ] Retry logic with exponential backoff implemented\n518: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n519: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n520: - [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented and tested\n521: - [ ] Integration with client-go informers and listers verified\n522: - [ ] Workqueue rate limiting functional\n523: - [ ] Events recorded for significant reconciliation actions\n524: - [ ] Configuration via flags and environment variables\n525: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n526: \n527: ## Dependencies\n528: \n529: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (client-go typed clients, informers, listers)\n530: - **Required**: CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) registered and served\n531: - **Required**: RBAC permissions for watching CRDs and managing Pods\n532: - **Required**: SharedInformerFactory operational\n533: - **Related**: AR-004 (HTTP server) - reconciler runs alongside HTTP server\n\n(End of file - total 533 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n  - Document each method purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849592349,"end":1775849592387}}}}
