{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849676731,"sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","part":{"id":"prt_d78e26727001xwpswR1U0SNH5T","messageID":"msg_d78e25680001T9Qnfq6D6oIaxF","sessionID":"ses_2871e02baffeVS1qV05Pg80Yc4","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_6c35599f7a5a49cb96c8ae64","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Session Data Structures\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/session/types.go`\n  - Define `Session` struct with fields: `ID`, `Namespace`, `Kind`, `BackendName`, `BackendURL`, `UserID`, `CreatedAt`, `LastActivityAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `State`, `Metadata`, `mu`\n  - Define `SessionState` type with consts: `SessionStateActive`, `SessionStateIdle`, `SessionStateExpired`, `SessionStateTerminated`\n  - Define `SessionConfig` struct with all configuration fields\n  - Define `RedisSessionConfig` struct\n  - Add `GenerateSessionID()` helper function\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `pkg/router/session/config.go`\n  - Implement `DefaultSessionConfig()` function\n  - Implement config validation method `Validate()`\n  - Implement environment variable loading\n\n### Phase 2: Session Store Interface\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/router/session/store.go`\n  - Define `SessionStore` interface with methods: `Get()`, `Set()`, `Delete()`, `List()`, `ListByUser()`, `Close()`\n  - Define error types: `ErrSessionNotFound`, `ErrSessionStoreError`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Create `pkg/router/session/memory_store.go`\n  - Implement `MemoryStore` struct with `sync.Map` and `sync.RWMutex`\n  - Implement all `SessionStore` interface methods\n  - Implement thread-safe concurrent access\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Create `pkg/router/session/redis_store.go`\n  - Implement `RedisStore` struct with redis client and config\n  - Implement `NewRedisStore()` constructor\n  - Implement all `SessionStore` interface methods\n  - Implement Redis key schema per design spec\n  - Implement connection pool configuration\n\n### Phase 3: Session Manager\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/session/manager.go`\n  - Define `SessionManager` struct with fields: `config`, `store`, `metrics`, `stopCh`, `wg`, `mu`\n  - Define `SessionMetrics` struct with Prometheus metrics\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewSessionManager()` constructor\n  - Takes config and store\n  - Creates metrics\n  - Returns initialized *SessionManager\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `SessionManager.CreateSession()` method\n  - Creates new session with provided parameters\n  - Generates session ID\n  - Stores session in store\n  - Records metrics\n  - Returns *Session or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `SessionManager.GetSession()` method\n  - Retrieves session from store by ID\n  - Checks expiration\n  - Updates last activity timestamp\n  - Returns *Session or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `SessionManager.UpdateSession()` method\n  - Updates session metadata\n  - Stores updated session\n\n- [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `SessionManager.DeleteSession()` method\n  - Terminates session\n  - Removes from store\n  - Records metrics\n\n- [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `SessionManager.ListSessions()` method\n  - Lists sessions matching filters\n  - Supports namespace, kind, userID filters\n\n- [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `SessionManager.CleanupExpiredSessions()` method\n  - Scans for expired sessions\n  - Removes expired sessions\n  - Returns count of cleaned sessions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `SessionManager.Start()` method\n  - Starts background cleanup loop\n  - Runs initial cleanup\n\n- [ ] **TASK-029**: Implement `SessionManager.Shutdown()` method\n  - Stops cleanup loop\n  - Waits for background tasks\n  - Persists in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n  - Closes store connection\n\n### Phase 4: Session Middleware\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/middleware/session_middleware.go`\n  - Define `SessionMiddleware` struct with manager and config\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.ExtractSession()` method\n  - Extracts session token from cookie\n  - Falls back to header if cookie not present\n  - Returns session ID or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.AttachSession()` method\n  - Sets session cookie on response\n  - Configures cookie properties (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.WithSession()` method\n  - Wraps HTTP handler with session context\n  - Validates session token\n  - Attaches session to request context\n\n### Phase 5: Session Integration with Router\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/session_resolver.go`\n  - Implement `ResolveWithSession()` method\n  - Check session affinity\n  - Reassign backend if unhealthy\n  - Update session last activity\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement session affinity algorithm\n  - Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n  - Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Update `pkg/router/handler.go`\n  - Integrate session middleware\n  - Pass session to resolver\n\n### Phase 6: Session Management Endpoints\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Create `pkg/router/session_handler.go`\n  - Define `SessionHandler` struct\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement session management HTTP handlers\n  - `ListSessionsHandler()` - GET /sessions\n  - `GetSessionHandler()` - GET /sessions/{id}\n  - `CreateSessionHandler()` - POST /sessions\n  - `DeleteSessionHandler()` - DELETE /sessions/{id}\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement error response format\n  - Define `SessionErrorResponse` struct\n  - Define error codes constants\n\n### Phase 7: Error Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Create `pkg/router/session_errors.go`\n  - Define session error types:\n    - `ErrSessionNotFound`, `ErrSessionExpired`, `ErrSessionTerminated`\n    - `ErrSessionCreateFailed`, `ErrSessionStoreError`\n    - `ErrBackendUnavailable`, `ErrAffinityBroken`\n    - `ErrInvalidSessionConfig`, `ErrRedisConnectionFailed`\n  - Define error codes constants\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement fallback strategy\n  - Define `FallbackStrategy` type\n  - Implement graceful degradation logic\n\n### Phase 8: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - Session Types\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestSession_IsExpired` in `pkg/router/session/session_test.go`\n  - Given: Session with ExpiresAt in the past\n  - When: IsExpired() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestSession_IsIdle`\n  - Given: Session with LastActivityAt exceeding idle timeout\n  - When: IsIdle() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestSession_UpdateActivity`\n  - Given: Active session\n  - When: UpdateActivity() called\n  - Then: LastActivityAt updated to now\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestSession_ThreadSafety`\n  - Given: Session accessed from multiple goroutines\n  - When: Concurrent reads and writes\n  - Then: No data race\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestGenerateSessionID`\n  - Given: Multiple calls to GenerateSessionID()\n  - When: IDs generated\n  - Then: All IDs are unique, follow format `sess_<timestamp>_<random>`\n\n#### Unit Tests - Memory Store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestMemoryStore_GetSet` in `pkg/router/session/memory_store_test.go`\n  - Given: Memory store\n  - When: Set() then Get()\n  - Then: Returns stored session\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestMemoryStore_Delete`\n  - Given: Session in store\n  - When: Delete() called\n  - Then: Get() returns ErrSessionNotFound\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestMemoryStore_List`\n  - Given: Multiple sessions with different namespaces/kinds\n  - When: List() with filters\n  - Then: Returns matching sessions\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestMemoryStore_ListByUser`\n  - Given: Sessions for multiple users\n  - When: ListByUser() called\n  - Then: Returns sessions for specified user\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess`\n  - Given: Memory store\n  - When: Concurrent Get/Set/Delete from multiple goroutines\n  - Then: No data race, all operations succeed\n\n#### Unit Tests - Redis Store\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestRedisStore_GetSet` in `pkg/router/session/redis_store_test.go`\n  - Given: Redis store with test Redis server\n  - When: Set() then Get()\n  - Then: Returns stored session\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestRedisStore_Delete`\n  - Given: Session in Redis\n  - When: Delete() called\n  - Then: Session removed\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: `TestRedisStore_List`\n  - Given: Multiple sessions in Redis\n  - When: List() with filters\n  - Then: Returns matching sessions\n\n- [ ] **TEST-023**: `TestRedisStore_ListByUser`\n  - Given: Sessions for multiple users in Redis\n  - When: ListByUser() called\n  - Then: Returns sessions for specified user\n\n- [ ] **TEST-024**: `TestRedisStore_ConnectionFailure`\n  - Given: Invalid Redis address\n  - When: NewRedisStore() called\n  - Then: Returns error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-025**: `TestRedisStore_KeyExpiration`\n  - Given: Session with short TTL\n  - When: TTL expires\n  - Then: Session automatically removed\n\n#### Unit Tests - Session Manager\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestSessionManager_CreateSession` in `pkg/router/session/manager_test.go`\n  - Given: Configured SessionManager\n  - When: CreateSession() called\n  - Then: Session created, stored, metrics recorded\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestSessionManager_GetSession`\n  - Given: Existing session\n  - When: GetSession() called\n  - Then: Session returned, LastActivityAt updated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestSessionManager_GetSession_Expired`\n  - Given: Expired session\n  - When: GetSession() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrSessionExpired, session cleaned up\n\n- [ ] **TEST-033**: `TestSessionManager_DeleteSession`\n  - Given: Existing session\n  - When: DeleteSession() called\n  - Then: Session removed, metrics recorded\n\n- [ ] **TEST-034**: `TestSessionManager_ListSessions`\n  - Given: Multiple sessions\n  - When: ListSessions() with filters\n  - Then: Returns matching sessions\n\n- [ ] **TEST-035**: `TestSessionManager_CleanupExpiredSessions`\n  - Given: Mix of active and expired sessions\n  - When: CleanupExpiredSessions() called\n  - Then: Only expired sessions removed, count returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-036**: `TestSessionManager_SessionAffinity`\n  - Given: Session bound to backend\n  - When: Session accessed\n  - Then: Returns same backend\n\n- [ ] **TEST-037**: `TestSessionManager_ConcurrentAccess`\n  - Given: SessionManager with multiple sessions\n  - When: Concurrent Create/Get/Delete from multiple goroutines\n  - Then: No data race, all operations succeed\n\n#### Unit Tests - Session Middleware\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: `TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Cookie` in `pkg/router/middleware/session_middleware_test.go`\n  - Given: Request with session cookie\n  - When: ExtractSession() called\n  - Then: Returns session ID from cookie\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: `TestSessionMiddleware_ExtractSession_Header`\n  - Given: Request with X-AgentCube-Session header\n  - When: ExtractSession() called\n  - Then: Returns session ID from header\n\n- [ ] **TEST-042**: `TestSessionMiddleware_AttachSession`\n  - Given: New session\n  - When: AttachSession() called\n  - Then: Response has correct Set-Cookie header\n\n- [ ] **TEST-043**: `TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_Success`\n  - Given: Valid session token\n  - When: WithSession() wraps handler\n  - Then: Handler receives session in context\n\n- [ ] **TEST-044**: `TestSessionMiddleware_WithSession_InvalidToken`\n  - Given: Invalid session token\n  - When: WithSession() wraps handler\n  - Then: Returns 401/404 error\n\n#### Unit Tests - Session Resolver\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: `TestResolver_ResolveWithSession_Success` in `pkg/router/resolver_test.go`\n  - Given: Session bound to healthy backend\n  - When: ResolveWithSession() called\n  - Then: Returns session's backend\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: `TestResolver_ResolveWithSession_Reassign`\n  - Given: Session bound to unhealthy backend\n  - When: ResolveWithSession() called\n  - Then: Returns different healthy backend\n\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: `TestResolver_ResolveWithSession_NoSession`\n  - Given: No session\n  - When: ResolveWithSession() called\n  - Then: Returns least loaded backend\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-060**: `TestSessionManager_RedisPersistence` in `pkg/router/session/session_integration_test.go`\n  - Use real Redis or testcontainers\n  - Create session\n  - Restart store\n  - Verify session persisted\n\n- [ ] **TEST-061**: `TestSessionManager_SessionExpiration`\n  - Create session with short MaxDuration\n  - Wait for expiration\n  - Verify session cleaned up\n\n- [ ] **TEST-062**: `TestSessionManager_ConcurrentSessionAccess`\n  - Simulate 100+ concurrent sessions\n  - Verify no data races\n  - Verify performance < 1ms p99\n\n- [ ] **TEST-063**: `TestSessionManager_CleanupRoutine`\n  - Start SessionManager with short cleanup interval\n  - Create expired sessions\n  - Verify cleanup runs and removes them\n\n- [ ] **TEST-064**: `TestSessionManager_Failover`\n  - Given: Redis connection lost\n  - When: Fallback to memory store\n  - Then: Operations continue with degraded mode\n\n#### Performance Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-070**: `BenchmarkSessionManager_CreateSession` in `pkg/router/session/session_bench_test.go`\n  - Benchmark session creation latency\n\n- [ ] **TEST-071**: `BenchmarkSessionManager_GetSession`\n  - Benchmark session lookup latency\n\n- [ ] **TEST-072**: `BenchmarkSessionStore_Redis`\n  - Benchmark Redis store operations\n\n- [ ] **TEST-073**: `BenchmarkSessionStore_Memory`\n  - Benchmark memory store operations\n\n#### Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-080**: Create `newTestSession()` helper in `pkg/router/session/session_test.go`\n  - Creates session with specified parameters for testing\n\n- [ ] **TEST-081**: Create `newTestSessionConfig()` helper\n  - Returns default test configuration\n\n- [ ] **TEST-082**: Create `newTestRedisConfig()` helper\n  - Returns test Redis configuration\n\n- [ ] **TEST-083**: Create `MockSessionStore` for testing\n  - Implements SessionStore interface with mock behavior\n\n- [ ] **TEST-084**: Setup test Redis server using miniredis\n  - Provides in-memory Redis for testing\n\n### Phase 9: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/session/doc.go`\n  - Package overview\n  - Session management architecture\n  - Configuration options\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n  - Document parameters, return values\n  - Document error conditions\n  - Include examples where applicable\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/middleware/doc.go`\n  - Middleware architecture\n  - Usage examples\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Document session lifecycle in code comments\n  - State transitions\n  - Expiration logic\n  - Cleanup strategy\n\n- [ ] **DOC-005**: Update `pkg/router/README.md`\n  - Add session management section\n  - Document configuration options\n  - List environment variables\n\n- [ ] **DOC-006**: Verify `pkg/router/AR-010-session-management.md` is complete\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Session can be created, retrieved, updated, deleted\n- [ ] Session expiration enforced (idle timeout, max duration)\n- [ ] Session affinity maintained for backend routing\n- [ ] Redis store persists sessions for recovery\n- [ ] Memory store works for dev/test environments\n- [ ] Session middleware extracts/attaches session tokens\n- [ ] Background cleanup removes expired sessions\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown persists/cleans up sessions\n- [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus monitoring\n- [ ] All unit tests pass with ≥85% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real Redis\n- [ ] Performance: Session lookup overhead < 1ms p99\n- [ ] Scalability: Support 10,000+ concurrent sessions\n- [ ] Thread-safe concurrent access verified\n- [ ] Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes\n- [ ] Graceful degradation on Redis failure\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n- [ ] Environment variables documented\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | External | Redis client |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | External | Metrics |\n| `pkg/router` (AR-009) | Internal | Router base module |\n| `github.com/go-redsync/miniredis` | External | Test Redis server |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012\n                              ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → ... → TASK-029\n                              ↓\nTASK-030 → TASK-031 → TASK-032 → TASK-033\n                              ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042\n                              ↓\nTASK-050 → TASK-051 → TASK-052\n                              ↓\nTASK-060 → TASK-061\n                              ↓\nTEST-001 → ... → TEST-084\n                              ↓\nDOC-001 → ... → DOC-006\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775849676716,"end":1775849676727}}}}
